<!-- Trust Engine -->
Trust engine is the most NGO-specific thing in the entire system.
Its job is to receive incoming money and immediately partition it into fund pools before anything else can touch it. When you receive Ksh 5M from a donor, that amount becomes a liability in your ledger — not income.
It only converts to income as you execute milestones and spend against it. This is called deferred revenue recognition, and it's a hard legal requirement from most institutional donors. The audit trail vault ties every expenditure back to a specific grant line.


